messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full path: /api/products/{id}

- all HTTP methods acceptable: false

- HEAD acceptable: false
- POST acceptable: false
- OPTIONS acceptable: false
- TRACE acceptable: false
- GET acceptable: true
- PUT acceptable: true
- DELETE acceptable: true
- PATCH acceptable: false

Explanation:
- server.js mounts the product router at the prefix /api/products: app.use('/api/products', productRoutes).
- In routes/productRoutes.js the route for ':id' is defined as:
  - .get(checkObjectId, getProductById)
  - .put(protect, admin, checkObjectId, updateProduct)
  - .delete(protect, admin, checkObjectId, deleteProduct)
  Therefore the concrete path is /api/products/:id (express path parameter id → {id}).
- The controller implementing the GET behavior is getProductById in controllers/productController.js.
- There is no router.route('/:id').post(...) or .patch(...) or .options(...) or .head(...), nor any router.all or app.all that would allow all methods — so POST, PATCH, OPTIONS, TRACE, and HEAD are not accepted based on the source code.
- PUT and DELETE are registered (protected by protect and admin middleware), so they are accepted.
- GET is registered (with checkObjectId middleware), so it is accepted.
